title: Grateful Dead Live at Shrine Auditorium on 1976-10-14
description: Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Cassidy, Peggy-O, Big River, Ramble On Rose, Looks Like Rain, Deal, El Paso, Tennessee Jed, The Music Never Stopped, Scarlet Begonias Minglewood Blues, Mississippi Half Step, Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Dancin' In The Streets-> Wharf Rat-> Dancin' In The Streets-> Around & Around, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: Solid show Yet another show I had on tape long long ago and great to find a better quality CD of. The quality could be better, but as soon as you start listening to the Dancin'>Wharf Rat>Dancin', all that is quickly forgotten. Download is definitely worth it just for those tunes.

This AUD SLAAAAYS!! Man, these Shrine shows are so dope. Like it says in the notes, this is one of the best sounding 76 AUD tapes, and the Dead rip this one to shreds, esp. from Scarlet on. Don't sleep! SHN only, I think the compression hits the AUD shows harder than SBDs.
Oh Yeah! Jaw-droppingly fierce Scarlet Begonias, best stand-alone version I can think of at the moment - get it!  Second set just rolls from there...

My first show! Wow!!! this concert was legendary for me!  The mysterious ambience of the Dead and the Shrine are just burned into my memory of that night.. Fantastic song selection...so many highlights of Jerry firing on all cylinders...woo hoo.. Thank you for this Mr. Bertrand!

Also my first show . This AUD really sounds like what it sounded like at the Shrine that night . I realize now this was not a stellar show, but I enjoyed it while I was there !
Others have mentioned, the "Dancin'>Wharf Rat>Dancin'" (the second of 2 of these), and the "Scarlet" , which should catch the ear of a more experienced/ jaded Dead listener . The 3 stars I am giving it, is relative to other 76 shows, but  I would like to give the sound for the AUD 4 .
A swell dance concert Put on the Dancin' > Wharf Rat > Dancin' > Around and Around and Johnny B. Goode of this AUD and play it LOUD.
Show time? Anyone know what time the music started?
